Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Demosthenes” 7; δ. σώματός τε καὶ τόνου φωνῆς 3rd c.AD: Longinus Rhetor “Ars Rhetorica” p.194H. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>disposition</b> of property, <b>will, testament,</b> ={διαθήκη}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator “Fragmenta” 44, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 922b. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> <b>disposing of, sale,</b> τῶν περιόντων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 11.14, compare “PTeb.” 38.10 (2nd c.BC), 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 11.2.12, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Solon” 24 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οἷς δ. εὔπορος, perhaps <b>means of disposing of</b> it, <b>of making away with</b> it, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1372a33 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] (possibly, <b>inventive disposition</b>). <br /><Level3><b>__5</b></Level3> δ. ἔγγραφος written <b>report,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" POxy. 52.13 (4th c.AD). \">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__6</b></Level3> ={διάθεμα}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.AD: Proclus Philosophus \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]<b>inCra.</b>p.10P.(<i>plural</i>). <br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> (from <i>passive</i>) <b>bodily state, condition,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἀρχαίης ἰητρικῇς” 7, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Generatione Animalium” 778b34; δ. τοῦ σώματος 4th-3rd c.BC: Philemo Comicus 95.4 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; δ. ὑγιεινή, νοσώδης, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 5.826, 17(2).238\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; ἕξις defined as δ. μόνιμος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 5.826; νευρικὴ δ. “OGI” 331.11 (Pergam.) \">Refs</a>]; of the mind, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Antipho Sophista 24a; ἕξις ψυχῆς καὶ δ. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Philebus” 11d \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; distinguished from ἕξις, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Categoriae” 8b28, “de An.” 417b15, Zeno and 3rd c.BC: Chrysippus Stoicus 1.50, 3.111; δ. ἁμαρτωλός 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “περὶ παρρησίας” p.560., +others\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; δ. σωματική, ψυχική, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Apollonius Dyscolus Grammaticus “de Syntaxi;” 278.10: _plural_, Diotogenes Philosophus cited in 5th c.AD: Stobaeus, Joannes 4.7.62. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.b</b></Level4> <b>disposition</b> towards persons, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 489a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>propensity,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Cicero, M. Tullius Orator et Philosophus “Epistulae ad Atticum” 14.3.2 \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]; πρός τινα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"Scholia 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 8. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> generally, <b>state, condition,</b> τὴν βασιγείαν εἰς τὴν ἀρχαίαν δ. κατέστησεν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “OGI” 219.11 (Sigeum, 4th-3rd c.BC). \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> Grammars, <b>force, function,</b> τοῦ ὀνόματος δ. εἰσὶ δύο, ἐνέργεια καὶ πάθος (e.g. κριτής, κριτός) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Dionysius Thrax Grammaticus 637.29 \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; especially of the <b>voices</b> of the verb, δ. εἰσὶ τρεῖς, ἐνέργεια, πάθος, μεσότης [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 638.8 \">Refs</a>]; δ. παθητική, μέση, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Apollonius Dyscolus Grammaticus “de Syntaxi;” 210.19, 226.10; also of tense, χρονικὴ δ. [prev. work] 251.1 (assuming variant)\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; διαβατικὴ δ. transitive <b>force,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 43.18. \">Refs</a>]","strongNumber":"G6827","accentedUnicode":"διάθεσις","shortDef":"a disposition","mediumDef":"a disposition","stepGloss":"a disposition","stepTransliteration":"diathesis","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}